<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB06339</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT STRENGTHENING THE FILIPINO YOUTH INVOLVEMENT IN AGRICULTURE AND ENTREPRENEURSHIP</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : "Young Agripreneurs Act of 2020"
Aims to address the state of unemployment, underemployment and the condition of rural youths who are forced to work in urban communities.

Intends to create a  "Youth Agricultural Hubs" in provinces and highly urbanized cities which shall: 
be the center for trainings, assistance, and opportunities; monitor and evaluate programs, projects, 
and activities; and facilitate partnerships among stakeholders, in the promotion of youth involvement 
in agriculture.

Proposes the conduct of series of "Youth Agripreneurship Trade Fairs" showcasing the youth's agricultural products; and appropriates three percent (3%) of Internal Revenue Allotment of the LGU concerned for youth's hubs.
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>TAN, SHAREE ANN T.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2020-02-19</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Teves (J.) (000 2020-03-11)</td><td>2. Lazatin (000 2020-03-11)</td><tr><td>3. Sy-Alvarado (000 2020-03-09)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON YOUTH AND SPORTS DEVELOPMENT ON 2020-02-24</td></tr></table>